definitions.definition: A rank in the classification of organisms , below kingdom and above class ; also called a divisio or a division , especially in describing plants ; a taxon at that rank
examples: Mammals belong to the phylum Chordata.

definitions.definition: A large division of possibly related languages, or a major language family which is not subordinate to another.

main_definition: ( taxonomy ) A rank in the classification of organisms , below kingdom and above class ; also called a divisio or a division , especially in describing plants ; a taxon at that rank
